name: Leaf Tornado
description:
As summer comes to an end and the leaves begin to change color, I'm reminded of the leaf tornados I used to see as a kid. I remember watching a gust of wind blow through a pile of leaves, picking it up and carrying it across the yard. This piece invokes the feelings of autumn and the playfulness of falling leaves.

(Move the cursor around the canvas to control the leaf tornado and click to reset the canvas)
